<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
The melanic colour form of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. ferrugatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="ferrugatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. ferrugatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described by Konow as 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. thomsoni subsp. var. var. miricolor" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="variety" species="thomsoni" subSpecies="var." variety="miricolor">D. thomsoni var. miricolor</taxonomicName>
, has sometimes been mixed up with 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. pachycerus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="pachycerus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. pachycerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hartig, 1837. Apart from their different penis valves, they can be separated by the shape and the structure of the mesoscutellar appendage: long, concave at the sides, and with a distinct longitudinal keel in 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. pachycerus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="pachycerus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. pachycerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
compared with 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. ferrugatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="ferrugatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. ferrugatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
